def: Of or pertaining to the chin and lower jaw.-- n.
The state of desponding; loss of hope and cessation of effort;discouragement; depression or dejection of the mind.The unhappy prince seemed, during some days, to be sunk indespondency. Macaulay.
Liquefying by heat after having been frozen; thawing; melting.
Pertaining to lithophosphor; becoming phosphoric by heat.

A high priest. Especially:(a) One of the sacred college, in ancient Rome, which had the supremejurisdiction over all matters of religion, at the head of which wasthe Pontifex Maximus. Dr. W. Smith.(b) (Jewish Antiq.) The chief priest.(c) (R. C. Ch.) The pope.
A troop; a company. [Obs. or Poetic]Legions and cohorts, turms of horse and wings. Milton.
To set forth as a known quantity or a known relation, or as apremise from which to reason; -- used principally in the passive formgiven.
